Key Investment Highlights

After a solid track record of performance, the business has generated $25.5M in Net Sales at 10% Gross Profit last year and is currently on track to generate $27.2M in Net Sales at 20.7% Gross Profit this financial year as a result of the following key initiatives:


  • Major distribution agreement signed with Monde Nissin in Australia to launch in February 2024
  • 3x NEW owned & developed ‘better-for-you’ brands to launch in major Australian retailers - REMIXT® (December 2023), THE GOOD BREKKIE® (January 2024) & PACE® (May 2024) in partnership with Aussie Cricket Captain Pat Cummins.

The business has also laid the groundwork for rapid global expansion with EMEA regional manufacturing in place. It is forecasting $42.2M in Net Sales at 26.2% Gross Profit and an inaugural positive EBITDA of $3.5M by the end of FY25, positioning it strongly for continued global product and channel expansion.

The company intends to conduct an institutional capital raise at a significantly higher valuation to fast-track its global growth strategy within 18 months. This raise is also expected to create a liquidity event for investors in this round.

The company is offering select investors an opportunity to take an equity position in the company in advance of that liquidity, at an attractive 12% yield paid monthly in arrears and a 20% capital uplift within 18 months.

From the Founders: Cheers to you!

The world has evolved & as founders so have we.

13 years in and while NEXBA has not been immune to what many describe as an unprecedented & challenging environment (COVID & geo-political issues resulting in global supply chain constraints, rising inflation, and instability in capital markets), it has cemented the growing market opportunity to deliver our vision. During the last 3 years, we have maintained our strong domestic customer relationships and category presence, and built internationally, adding distribution in 9 new countries for NEXBA. We have the experience to deliver a multi-market, multi-channel, multi-category portfolio of leading 'better-for-you' brands.

As founders we are proud of our team and our shareholders. We thank them & you for being a part of our NEXBA story. The NEXBA brand has set the foundations for our expansion to GOODNESS GROUP GLOBAL.

This next phase has already seen a step–change in execution excellence as we seek to capitalise on our strong customer partnerships, proprietary Goodsweet® sweetener & growing consumer demand for 'better-for-you' brands.

While sustainable growth will always be an important metric - accelerating profitability & scaling up impact is our commitment to maximising value for shareholders long-term.

Cheers to you!

The Offer

With a $5,000 minimum investment, diversify your portfolio and earn fixed income via Convertible Notes in Goodness Group Global, with a Coupon of 12% p.a. paid monthly in arrears.

  • Round Size: Up to $5M
  • Coupon: 12% p.a. paid monthly
  • Term: 18 months
  • Conversion: Automatic conversion into Ordinary Equity at a 20% discount to:
    • the valuation set by an external lead
    • if there is no qualifying capital raise or liquidity event within 18 months, at $1.28 per ordinary share (existing ordinary share value
    • Converted Equity will be held by VentureCrowd Nominees PTY Ltd as nominee.

Use of Funds and Exit Strategy

This ‘Series B’ capital raise extension offers the business the opportunity to execute a bolder business plan, to focus on delivering profitability in each division and ultimately create a stronger Goodness Group Global platform that will unlock greater value and liquidity options for all shareholders over time.

The founders are seeking investors who share their vision to create positive change with brands that Taste Good & Do Good.

The founders’ ambition is to continue the business beyond the next phase, further delivering internal governance and management expertise to enhance accountability and performance in mitigating risks and unlocking expansion opportunities.

Goodness Group Global is pursuing a final short-term capital raise from existing shareholders and select aligned new investors who would represent a minority investment in the Group.

The Group aims to return to the capital markets at a superior valuation once they deliver on the business plan and expansion opportunities outlined. The Founders anticipate this to be a 3 to 5-year horizon and it is at this point they expect the opportunity for a significant liquidity event for all shareholders.

What is Goodness Group Global

NEXBA is the only multi-category brand with a patented all-natural, sugar-free (Goodsweet® sweetener) alternative to sugar & artificial ingredient use. The promise of guilt-free enjoyment connects with a consumer mindset that is universal across demographics, life-stage groups, beverage needs and occasions.

The existing business behind the iconic Australian-owned brand NEXBA has evolved into purpose-driven Goodness Group Global. The Group will fill the gap for a 'better-for-you' food & beverage platform built on a portfolio of complementary high-performing brands triggering liquidity options for investors as they grow, with Founders retaining meaningful ownership.

The opportunity to invest has grown beyond NEXBA, with new expansion opportunities via M&A, Build, & License strategy for new brands & products under Goodness Group Global - including leveraging proprietary Goodsweet® branded natural sweetener, Goodness Synergy Drivers including new brands and products sharing costs, new distribution channels & markets, and Manufacturing collaboration at scale.

Why NEXBA Expansion to Goodness Group Global

In 2023 the founders & shareholders of NEXBA formed Goodness Group Global. Goodness Group Global’s purpose is ‘creating change for good, one sip and bite at a time!’

Goodness Group Global will be a multi-market, multi-category brand platform, proudly owned by passionate founders, underpinned by iconic Australian challenger brand NEXBA and powered by its proprietary and proven Goodsweet® sweetener.

The health and wellness megatrend: Health, wellness and sustainability have become global megatrends, with FoodTech and BevTech fast becoming two of the most important emerging investment sectors.

Consumers and the planet deserve better: However, the food and beverage industry is dominated by multinationals who have failed to put the health and wellness of consumers first. Goodness Group Global is committed to being founder-driven with brands that, at their core, taste good and do good.

Put frankly, Goodness Group Global wants multinational food & beverage corporations to take notice and rethink sugar, artificial ingredient use & what is ‘good for the planet’.

Under Goodness Group Global, NEXBA will continue to champion the movement to remove sugar and artificials from consumption and the Goodsweet® sweetener will unlock incremental opportunities. Together, Goodness Group Global will transform health and wellness as the total brand portfolio will reduce sugar and artificial ingredient consumption in key food and beverage categories.

More accessible 'better-for-you' brands mean more growth: Founded with purpose-led Australian brand, NEXBA, Goodness Group Global can create a step-jump in the value of the business as they activate synergies to make 'better-for-you' and the planet products more accessible and available to consumers.

Understanding The Goodsweet Difference

Their unique and universally applicable proprietary ‘Goodsweet®’ sweetener blend, developed over 6 years, allows NEXBA to emulate the taste profile of sugar in an unprecedented and all-natural way. The Goodness Group Global will deliver further innovation with NEXBA brand & future-owned brands & license Goodsweet® as an ingredient.

Goodsweet® is differentiated by adding secret natural ingredients to its natural sweetener blend that makes the taste profile unparalleled to the competition.

Stevia/Erythritol-based blends are not new to the market. However, they do not emulate the taste profile of sugar.

Goodsweet® is differentiated by adding secret natural ingredients to its sweetener blend that makes the taste profile unparalleled to the competition. After intensive sweetness is removed, only the natural, plant-based building blocks of Goodsweet® remain.

Goodsweet® Sweetener is the ‘intel chip’ to ensure ‘no added sugar’ or ‘artificials’ exist within Goodness Group Global. Brands & Products can contain naturally occurring sugars that are good for you.

The Group's Proprietary Sweetener Blend is fully transferable to other food & beverage products with the same outcomes around sweetness, mouthfeel and aftertaste.

The Group continues to invest in and lead the development of the next generation of Goodsweet® & an ongoing strategic patenting process.

Problem and Market

Consumers are gradually shifting towards sugar-free, all natural alternatives and healthier functional drinks. Traditional soft drinks companies focus on cost minimization vs delivering better-for-you for consumers. With sugar avoidance hitting the mainstream, younger generations are becoming increasingly sceptical about how sugar-free taste is achieved, driving a shift towards natural and more progressive products that better reflect their needs.

NEXBA not only disrupts the massive Soft Drinks category by removing billions of grams of sugar whilst maintaining a great and authentic taste, but also can take the lead in fast moving better-for-you emerging categories.

NEXBA’s core category, Kombucha, has already developed sales of $270M1 AUD in home market Australia growing 20%2 with growth of over 40%2 projected in other key markets for NEXBA including the UK.
